This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) as it proposes a data-driven approach to estimate the 3D pose of a hand given a depth image. The use of Deep Networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the mention of implementation running on a GPU suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of multimedia (MM).
